a whole can of worms.

34:42.513 --> 34:45.615
I don't think
you wanna do that.

34:51.355 --> 34:54.791
Maryanne said
we're out of formula.

34:55.526 --> 34:56.726
Go.

34:56.728 --> 34:58.595
You, too, donner.
And harlan.

34:58.597 --> 35:01.731
Not gonna hear anything.
See you in the morning.

35:01.733 --> 35:03.200
Good night.

35:03.202 --> 35:04.801
Night.

35:06.170 --> 35:08.271
There's no point
in you staying either.

35:08.273 --> 35:10.240
Oh, I don't mind.

35:10.242 --> 35:12.109
I'm leaving myself.

35:13.077 --> 35:15.345
Oh! Well...

35:15.446 --> 35:19.483
I was expecting to go home
with my husband,
so I got a lift in.

35:19.485 --> 35:21.818
I need to call a cab.

35:27.058 --> 35:31.161
Next, he'll have us
pretending to wire them up.

35:31.163 --> 35:32.195
Actors!

35:32.197 --> 35:33.296
He needs cutaways.

35:33.298 --> 35:35.799
The entirety of your story
cannot be told

35:35.801 --> 35:37.968
With the two of you
sitting behind a table,

35:37.970 --> 35:40.804
Talking about things
that can't be shown on tv.

35:40.806 --> 35:42.806
A re-enactment
is a happy medium.

35:42.808 --> 35:44.708
I'm not happy
about any of this.

35:44.710 --> 35:47.043
It's fake, all of it,

35:47.045 --> 35:47.811
What I'm pretending to be,

35:47.813 --> 35:51.715
The fact
I'm selling something
that doesn't even exist.

35:51.717 --> 35:52.849
I am not a salesman, shep.

35:52.851 --> 35:55.819
Well, then, bill,
you're the only one,

35:55.821 --> 35:57.821
Because we are all
selling something.

35:57.823 --> 36:01.458
I sold you on me,
on what I could do for you.

36:01.460 --> 36:05.095
John rock sold more
than the birth control pill,

36:05.097 --> 36:06.463
He sold an idea,

36:06.465 --> 36:09.366
Of pleasure without
permanent consequence.

36:09.368 --> 36:10.867
He kicked open
the door for you,

36:10.869 --> 36:12.836
But you've got
to walk through it,

36:12.838 --> 36:14.638
Stake your claim
and say,

36:14.640 --> 36:15.872
"I'm in
the pleasure business, too."

36:15.874 --> 36:19.709
That is not my business.
I don't have a business.

36:19.711 --> 36:21.411
I have a study,
a practice,

36:21.413 --> 36:25.649
And I haven't
cured one single case
of sexual dysfunction.

36:25.651 --> 36:27.651
Yet, yet.

36:27.653 --> 36:29.286
But you will.

36:29.620 --> 36:31.655
And if you don't,
you tried.

36:31.657 --> 36:33.456
You got to reach
for it, bill,

36:33.458 --> 36:35.358
Even if it's
outside your grasp.

36:35.360 --> 36:38.195
It's the reaching
that people respect.

36:38.197 --> 36:39.996
Look, these two
presidential candidates,

36:39.998 --> 36:44.067
They may not
deliver a single thing
that they promise.

36:44.069 --> 36:46.369
I guarantee you
history will judge them

36:46.371 --> 36:49.139
Just as much
for the nobility
of their goals

36:49.141 --> 36:51.308
As for what
they actually achieved.

36:51.310 --> 36:53.643
But before any of that
can happen,

36:53.645 --> 36:56.513
One of them
has to come in first.

36:56.515 --> 36:58.315
You gotta be first, bill.

36:58.317 --> 37:01.351
That's what all of this
is about.

37:07.558 --> 37:10.360
Libby: There's usually news
at the top of the hour.

37:10.362 --> 37:12.362
(static over radio)

37:12.364 --> 37:14.731
(soft music playing)

37:17.902 --> 37:21.137
This is the station
you listen to?

37:21.572 --> 37:25.242
There won't be
any martin news
on this station.

37:25.244 --> 37:26.476
